 current karmas in =\r\nthose situations may further modify the momentum of the push (reaction) fro=\r\nm previous actions. Though one&#39;s current desires, actions and awareness are=\r\n actually the work of the all pervading shakti, they are also one&#39;s work in=\r\n a way. It depends on how we look at it and how we abstract it. Though Gang=\r\nes water in a bucket, Ganges water in a small cup, Ganges water in a cup in=\r\n hot weather and Ganges water in a cup in freezing weather are all Ganges w=\r\nater, they are different too. One is more, one is less, one is warm and one=\r\n is icy. Similarly, the work of all pervading shakti is&lt;BR&gt;different when e=\r\nxpressed through different vessels (people) in different\n situations.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B=\r\nR&gt;As long as one actually feels internally (despite what one may say or pre=\r\ntend externally) that one&#39;s desires, actions and knowledge are one&#39;s own, o=\r\nne is performing karmas and is bound to receive their kaarmik reactions. On=\r\nly when the&lt;BR&gt;realization that it is all the work of the all pervading sha=\r\nkti becomes full and completely internalized, does one become free from the=\r\n cycle of actions and reactions. Until then, all pervading shakti acts thro=\r\nugh one to give appropriate reactions to actions one thinks one is performi=\r\nng.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In astrological terms, horoscope is the sum total o=\r\nf previous karmas, whose fruits one will have to face. They show the circum=\r\nstances faced by one. They do not and cannot determine what actions one eng=\r\nages in, though certain actions are more likely in certain circumstances.&lt;B=\r\nR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Destiny is the sum total of the reactions to the actions committed by=\r\n one&#39;s free will. Today&#39;s actions of free will\n become destiny tomorrow (i.=\r\ne. on a future date or in a future life).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Best regards,&lt;BR&gt;Narasimha=\r\n&lt;BR&gt;----------------------